b) \(\displaystyle \frac{\sqrt[3]{72b^{2}}}{\sqrt[3]{9b^{5}}}\)

Combine the cube–roots:

\[
\frac{\sqrt[3]{72b^{2}}}{\sqrt[3]{9b^{5}}}
      =\sqrt[3]{\frac{72b^{2}}{9b^{5}}}
      =\sqrt[3]{8\,b^{\,2-5}}
      =\sqrt[3]{8\,b^{-3}}
      =\sqrt[3]{\frac{8}{b^{3}}}.
\]

Because \(8 = 2^{3}\) we have \(\sqrt[3]{8}=2\), and \(\sqrt[3]{b^{3}}=b\) (cube roots do not require an absolute-value symbol). Thus

\[
\sqrt[3]{\frac{8}{b^{3}}}
      =\frac{2}{b}, \qquad b\neq 0.
\]

Answer:  \(\displaystyle \frac{2}{b}\).

